"For us from IBM, this long-term thinking means a continental movement towards the future.
IBM survived and was also successful for a whole century because it remained true to its principles and did not hesitate to change everything else around it.
This allowed us to transform the technologies, business and society in the course of our first century.
We hope that we will do even more in the next hundred years," said Samuel J. Palmisano, the current director of the company on the occasion of the anniversary.
Contemplative system
Watson has already been providing social care for his employees in the 1930s - in a similar way as the entrepreneur Baťa in Czechoslovakia: The IBM people had paid vacations as one of the first American employees, an insurance by the entrepreneur plus elegant uniforms as work clothes and a well-thought-out pay system for the best new and dealer.
