In addition, be aware of the language of your subject.
Scott Peterson's exterminator is famous when he used the past when he claimed that his dead wife was still alive and triggered a national search for her.
Deceptive people can also use a distancing language: "I had no sexual relationship with this woman... Miss Lewinsky" or if you repeat a tricky question in total.
The most common verbal signs are subtle.
Some people use "qualifying language" when they answer a tricky question: "Well... to tell you the truth ... as far as I am known ... according to best knowledge and conscience."
