There are so many that I could talk about the bassists I like all afternoon.
How did Pearl Jam manage to keep the grunge alive, even though it is no longer a fashion appearance?
I think we all don't feel very connected with the word grunge.
When I think about it, I think of the bands that I mentioned earlier, such as Mudhoney, Soundgarden, Nirvana and all the others that came up at the same time. Even though they are important today, I think it’s great, because it’s worth listening to this music and bands like Mudhoney are making better music now than ever.
At first her music was darker, now she is more positive.
Why?
This is interesting, because I think there are a few songs on the new album that might seem a little light. But there are also other songs like The End or Just Breathe, which are classified as very dark songs, although they also have something positive in them.
